"title": "6733: repentance, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6733",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture stresses the necessity of repentance from sin if individuals and communities are to have full fellowship with God. It also uses the term to refer to God's relenting of sending judgment on his people, usually in response to human repentance.</p>\n<h2>Repentance is a requirement for fellowship with God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:13\">2KI 17:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:9\">1TH 1:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:14\">PSA 34:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:7\">ISA 55:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:15\">ACT 14:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:7-Jas4:10\">JAS 4:7–4:10</a></p>\n<h2>Repentance involves turning from sin</h2>\n<h3>Sorrow for sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:17\">PSA 51:17</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:8-2Cor7:10\">2CO 7:8–7:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:6\">JOB 42:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:18\">PSA 34:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa57:15\">ISA 57:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:2\">ISA 66:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:12-Joel2:13\">JOL 2:12–2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:13\">LUK 18:13</a></p>\n<h3>Confession of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:17-Luke15:19\">LUK 15:17–15:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:5\">LEV 5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:1-Ps51:3\">PSA 51:1–51:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:13\">PRO 28:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos14:1-Hos14:2\">HOS 14:1–14:2</a></p>\n<h3>Forsaking specific sins</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:10-Ezra10:11\">EZR 10:10–10:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek14:6\">EZK 14:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:19-Acts15:20\">ACT 15:19–15:20</a></p>\n<h3>Making appropriate restitution</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num5:6-Num5:7\">NUM 5:6–5:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:8\">LUK 19:8</a></p>\n<h2>Repentance involves turning to God</h2>\n<h3>Faith in God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:15\">ISA 30:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:32\">LUK 22:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:21\">ACT 11:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:21\">ACT 20:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:18\">ACT 26:18</a></p>\n<h3>Obedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:21-Ezek18:23\">EZK 18:21–18:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:7-Mal3:10\">MAL 3:7–3:10</a></p>\n<h3>Repentance demonstrated by actions</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:20\">ACT 26:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:16-Isa1:17\">ISA 1:16–1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:27\">DAN 4:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:8\">MAT 3:8</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:8\">LUK 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:10-Luke3:14\">LUK 3:10–3:14</a></p>\n<h2>Repentance must be sincere</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:10\">JER 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer24:7\">JER 24:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:46-1Kgs8:50\">1KI 8:46–8:50</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:36-2Chr6:39\">2CH 6:36–6:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:34-Ps78:37\">PSA 78:34–78:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:1-Hos6:4\">HOS 6:1–6:4</a></p>\n<h2>The repentance of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer26:3\">JER 26:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:14\">EXO 32:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:45\">PSA 106:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:8\">HOS 11:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:13\">JOL 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos7:1-Amos7:6\">AMO 7:1–7:6</a></p>",
